<% provide(:title, "Choose Template | Structure Wizard | " + @project.name) %>
<h1 align = "center"><%= @project.name + ": Choose Template" %></h1>
<div class="row">
 <%= form_tag({:action => 'choose_template'}, {:method => 'put', :name => 'choose_template', :class => "form-horizontal" } ) do %>
  <div class="row">
   <div class="span9 offset2">
    <p class="myfloat" align="justify">Choose one of the available templates below to create an initial data structure for your project. You can adapt groups and items later on.</p>
   </div>
   <div class="span7 offset3">
      <label class="radio">
        <%= radio_button :template, "selection", "SWOT" %><strong>SWOT Analysis</strong>
        <p class="myfloat">A structured planning method to evaluate the Strenghts, Weaknesses, Opportunities, and Threats of your project - <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SWOT_analysis">read more</a>.<br>
        This option is a good start for everybody using Hyve.me for the first time.</p>
      </label>
      <label class="radio">
        <%= radio_button :template, "selection", "Honeycomb" %><strong>Honeycomb Template</strong>
        <p class="myfloat">An advancement of the project management triangle in regard to validated learning - <a href="http://www.hyve.me/blog/?p=57">read more</a>.<br>
        This is also a general purpose template for any kind of project.</p>
      </label>
      <label class="radio">
        <%= radio_button :template, "selection", "Porter" %><strong>Porter's 5 Forces</strong>
        <p class="myfloat">A framework for industry analysis to evaluate the competitive intensity and attractiveness for a given market - <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Porter%27s_five_forces">read more</a>.<br>
        Use this option for business related projects.</p>
      </label>
      <label class="radio">
        <%= radio_button :template, "selection", "Lean" %><strong>Lean Canvas</strong>
        <p class="myfloat">A strategic management template to document activities and potential trade-offs - <a href="http://practicetrumpstheory.com/2012/02/why-lean-canvas/">read more</a>.<br>
        Use this option when you are evaluating new business models, e.g., a start-up.</p>
      </label>
      <label class="radio">
        <%= radio_button :template, "selection", "Thing" %><strong>Thiel's One Thing</strong>
        <p class="myfloat"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Thiel">Peter Thiel</a> recommends to focus on one singular thing - <a href="http://blog.idonethis.com/post/37113345206/peter-thiels-unorthodox-management-philosophy-of">read more</a>.<br>
        Use this option togehter with other templates to bring the most important thing you are working on today to mind.</p>
      </label>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
   </div>
   <div class="span9 offset2">
     <%= submit_tag("Cancel", :class => "btn btn-info btn-large pull-left", :id => "Cancel") %>
     <%= submit_tag(t('project.categoryNext'), :class => "btn btn-info btn-large pull-right", :id => "Next") %>
   </div>
  </div>
 <% end %>
 <p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>

